value.title: U.S. bishops approve "teaching document" that may rebuke Biden and other Catholic politicians who support abortion rights
value.excerpt: The decision came despite appeals from the Vatican for a more cautious and collegial approach to the divisive issue.

value.title: At risk of falling short on vaccine goal, Biden marks new milestone: 300M shots under his watch
value.excerpt: The White House is pointing to a new milestone on vaccinations – 300 million shots administered since President Joe Biden took office.

value.title: WV AG Morrisey sounds alarm on fentanyl overdose surge, points to Biden border policies
value.excerpt: West Virginia Attorney General Patrick Morrisey believes President Biden's decision to reverse the Trump administration's "remain in Mexico" policy has led to a spike in fentanyl trafficking and overdoses within the U.S.

value.title: Dem blasts Biden's decision to extend Canadian border restrictions another month: 'bulls---'
value.excerpt: New York lawmakers are irate over the White House’s decision to renew the Canada border shutdown for yet another month.

value.title: Pence met with jeers and called a "traitor" at Florida conservative conference

value.title: Donald Trump endorses Kelly Tshibaka for Senate in race against Lisa Murkowski
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump endorsed Alaska GOP Senate candidate Kelly Tshibaka on Friday, pledging to campaign against Republican Sen. Lisa Murkowski, who voted to convict him of inciting the deadly insurrection at the Capitol on January 6.

value.title: Pence called ‘traitor’ by hecklers at conservative Florida conference
value.excerpt: Former Vice President Mike Pence was heckled during his remarks at the Faith & Freedom Coalition’s annual gathering in Florida.

value.title: Pence criticizes Harris over declining to visit US-Mexico border
value.excerpt: Former Vice President Mike Pence took aim at his successor on Friday at a conference for religious conservatives in Florida, criticizing Vice President Kamala Harris for declining to visit the US-Mexico border during a recent immigration-focused trip to Central America.

value.title: Trump endorses Murkowski primary opponent Kelly Tshibaka
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump endorsed the primary opponent to Sen. Lisa Murkowski on Friday, declaring his support for Kelly Tshibaka Alaska's former commissioner of administration.

value.title: Trump's new chief spokeswoman, Liz Harrington, has been a serial promoter of election lies

value.title: Cruz rips Kamala Harris for avoiding border trip on 'Fox & Friends': Like a ‘comedy show’
value.excerpt: Ted Cruz, R- Texas, slammed the Biden administration for its inaction at the southern border on " Fox & Friends " Friday. Sen. Cruz said Vice President Kamala Harris ' failure to visit the border and avoidance of the topic is becoming like "a comedy show.

value.title: Trump was wrong about the law, Obamacare politics and his judges
value.excerpt: Analysis: The former president promised that his Supreme Court picks would overturn the Affordable Care Act. He met the court's ruling with the deafening silence of defeat.

value.title: Biden left to settle intra-party squabbles: The Note
value.excerpt: Congress is in the middle of a flurry of legislating, but it will fall to Biden in large part to define what he wants to do with the dwindling calendar.

value.title: Biden's 'off-limits' list for Russian cyberattacks criticized as 'green light' to target everything else
value.excerpt: President Biden's list of 16 key infrastructure entities that are “off-limits” to Russian cyberattacks has effectively given the Russians a green light to target everything not on that list without facing serious repercussions, national security experts and senior Republicans tell Fox News.

value.title: Back home: Biden has daunting to-do list after European tour
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden is facing a formidable to-do list now that he’s back from his summit-filled trip to Europe, with pressing legislative challenges, foreign policy follow-up and a need to steer the country’s reopening as the coronavirus threat recedes.

value.title: Dr. Ronny Jackson calls on Biden to immediately undergo cognitive test to assess 'mental impairment'
value.excerpt: Dr. Ronny Jackson, the former White House physician, called on President Biden to immediately undergo a cognitive test so the commander-in-chief can prove to the American public sound mental capabilities.

value.excerpt: U.S. District Judge Carl Nichols, who joined the court in 2019, will hear the Justice Department's lawsuit aimed at stopping insurance broker Aon's (AON.N) $30 billion acquisition of Willis Towers Watson (WTY.

value.title: Axios mocked for blaming worker burnout on Capitol riot, 'fallout from the Trump presidency'
value.excerpt: Many Americans have declined to return to work following coronavirus shutdowns and enhanced unemployment benefits, but Axios feels the labor shortage is largely former President Donald Trump’s fault.

value.title: Biden administration to invest $3 billion for Covid-19 antiviral medicines
value.excerpt: The Biden administration on Thursday announced it would invest more than $3 billion from the American Rescue Plan to accelerate the discovery, development and manufacturing of Covid-19 antiviral medicines -- ideally like a pill someone could easily take at home early in an illness.

value.title: Arizona sheriff says 'no distinct' border changes from Biden administration despite Sec. Mayorkas meetings
value.excerpt: An Arizona sheriff says there have been no changes in policy, messaging or results from the Biden administration on the crisis at the southern border -- despite multiple meetings between sheriffs and Homeland Security Secretary Alejandro Mayorkas.

value.title: Biden signs bill making Juneteenth a federal holiday
value.excerpt: Biden signs legislation making June 19, or Juneteenth, the 12th federal holiday. The day commemorates the end of slavery in this country.

value.title: White House cheers Supreme Court ObamaCare decision with nod to Biden's 'big f--- deal' hot mic comment
value.excerpt: The White House cheered the U.S. Supreme Court’s decision to uphold Obamacare, with a nod at President Biden’s 2010 “big f**king deal” reaction to then-President Obama signing the Affordable Care Act into law.

value.title: Lara Trump rips Biden for only taking questions from pre-approved reporters: 'Are you kidding me?'
value.excerpt: Fox News contributor Lara Trump tore into President Biden on Thursday for only taking pre-approved questions from reporters during a press conference following his meeting with Putin in Geneva.
